<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-10-15T17:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-08-19T18:00:00-05:00" n="32" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d32">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">Doc. No. 13 (G).</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Memorandum on the Clauses of the Draft Treaty
                                Concerning Bilateral Treaties</hi> (Art. 37.)</head>
                        <dateline>
                            <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content-and-sibling-dates" calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1946-10-15T23:59:59+01:00" notBefore="1946-08-20T00:00:00+01:00">undated</date>
                        </dateline>
                        <p rend="center"><hi rend="smallcaps">Article</hi> 37</p>
                        <p>According to Article 37 as worded in the Draft Treaty, each Allied or
                            Associated Power can, within 6 months of the coming into force of the
                            Treaty, notify Italy which pre-war bilateral treaties it desires to keep
                            in force or revive.</p>
                    </div>
